args: Mym gave us this box, but what is it?\n▷It's called a ＂jack-in-the-box.＂\nLuca had one just like it.◁
▷There's a spring inside that will\nmake something pop out!◁

Ah! It pops out really fast...
You'd be surprised if you opened it without
knowing.
I see. All you have to do is give this\nto someone and have them open it.\nIt seems like an easy prank.
▷Right. And since someone just arrived,\nit's time to give it a shot!◁
Alex, do you have a moment?
Of course. What do you need?
I have a request. Please open this box.
Er, can you not open it yourself?
I can open and close the box at will.
Sooo...why not just do that, then?
...I can't tell you the reason.\nI just want you to open it.
Oh, of course! This is a Halloween prank!\nWhich means this box is...
Ah, I knew it. It's a jack-in-the-box.
*grumble* Alex wasn't surprised...\n▷She figured it out before she even\nopened the thing! Prank failed.◁
Well, it WAS a terrifically obvious prank.
If you want to surprise someone with a\njack-in-the-box, you have to trick them\ninto opening it in a more natural way.
So I can't simply hand the box over.\nI have to trick them...
▷Yeah, now that you mention it, Luca\nalways had some crazy story ready when\nhe handed someone the jack-in-the-box.◁
▷He'd say something that caught their\ninterest and make them want to open it.◁
What should I say to tempt them into\nopening the box?

▷Well, I suppose it all depends
on the person you're talking to.◁
That doesn't tell me anything.
Answer clearly.
▷Actually, I'm not sure I CAN answer\nany more clearly that that, Laxi.\nSheesh! Tricking people is hard.◁
The rare occasion on which we agree.\nTricking people is indeed difficult.
But I won't give up on pranking.
I must successfully prank someone so I\ncan finally understand how such an\naction might bring them happiness.
Mascula, are there any pranks that can be\ndone without tricking someone?
▷Well, it seems like you have trouble\ntricking people with words, so maybe if\nyou didn't have to talk to them...?◁

I left the labels unchanged and swapped
the salt and sugar inside the containers.
Is that it?
▷Perfect!◁
▷Since this one is all planned in advance,\nyou can do it without talking to anyone!◁
Dear me, but I am busy. After the laundry,\nI still need to prepare supper.

This consommé is nearly translucent!
It doesn't get like this unless you're truly
diligent in skimming it. You are simply a
treasure, Cleo.
Best to eat it before it gets cold.
Good heavens! What is the matter?!
It appears this is one soup that Pipple\ndoes not wish to be cooked into.
Is our love for Cleo being tested?\nNever fear! I shall—
Hands off that spoon, buddy! Life's too\nshort to be shovin' terrible food into\nyer head hole.
Yo, Cleo, what's the deal? Did ya even\ntaste this before ya served it?
I fear I was too busy to do so—but it is\na recipe I know by heart, so the thought\nof it failing so badly is simply impossible.
What in the...? It's SWEET!\nBut I know I put salt into it!
Laxi! Did you replace my salt with sugar?!
Affirmative. That was me. Are you happy?
NO, I AM NOT HAPPY, LAXI!\nI AM NOT REMOTELY HAPPY!
This isn't a prank—it's a nuisance!
OF COURSE I AM!\nWHAT WERE YOU THINKING?!
(Just as I suspected: Playing pranks\nonly makes people angry at you.)
(Is it truly possible to make people happy\nwith such shenanigans?)
